284
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:46,600
Sey, Singha.
Go check on Singha first.

285
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:48,200
Go check on Sing.

286
00:23:50,840 --> 00:23:52,520
Sing.

287
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:00,600
Shit. Sing’s not breathing.

288
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:02,200
Singha.

289
00:24:02,760 --> 00:24:04,440
Singha.

290
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:07,200
You said you’d stay with me.

291
00:24:07,960 --> 00:24:10,680
Bro. Singha.

292
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:14,640
Sey, please help Singha.

293
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:21,240
Bro. Singha.

294
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:24,720
You’re my boyfriend now.

295
00:24:25,640 --> 00:24:28,080
You said you wouldn’t leave me.

296
00:24:29,520 --> 00:24:31,000
Singha.

297
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:35,120
Singha.

298
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:47,960
Is it true

299
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:50,520
the killer did this to extend his life.

300
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:52,560
Whatever the motive was,

301
00:24:52,560 --> 00:24:54,400
it’s my duty to enforce the law.

302
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:56,080
I have to do my job,

303
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:57,920
for public safety

304
00:24:57,960 --> 00:24:59,600
and peace.

305
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:01,120
Closing a case this big

306
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:02,880
is a major achievement.

307
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:06,440
Did the superintendent
lead the arrest himself.

308
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:09,120
Yeah, did you go on site personally.

309
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:15,000
We were able to close this case

310
00:25:15,360 --> 00:25:17,320
because of Inspector Singha.

311
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:21,920
I was just one member of the team.

312
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:24,600
And I’d like to ask the public

313
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:27,600
to keep Inspector Singha in your thoughts.
He’s critically injured

314
00:25:27,720 --> 00:25:29,200
from this case.

315
00:25:29,720 --> 00:25:31,680
We hope he recovers safely.

316
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:50,240
Even though his body is still functioning,

317
00:25:51,480 --> 00:25:54,280
there’s been no response at all.

318
00:25:55,280 --> 00:25:58,680
The doctor thinks the family
should prepare themselves.

319
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:38,200
I don’t want you going to work anymore.

320
00:26:39,360 --> 00:26:41,800
I just want to lock you in the condo,

321
00:26:42,680 --> 00:26:45,280
so you won’t have to risk
running into anything again.

322
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:55,640
Wouldn’t it be better to live together.

323
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:58,600
I don’t want to stay at the condo anymore.

324
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:18,120
Uh… have you heard anything about Singha.

325
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:24,520
He still hasn’t woken up.

326
00:27:27,360 --> 00:27:28,880
I don’t know what to do.

327
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:31,120
No one has any answers.

328
00:27:34,840 --> 00:27:36,840
I’ll take you to a temple.

329
00:27:37,360 --> 00:27:39,680
Let’s pray for Singha
to wake up soon.

330
00:27:41,600 --> 00:27:44,600
Should we do nine temples today.

331
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:47,160
It’s better than doing nothing.

332
00:27:49,520 --> 00:27:50,760
Trust me.

333
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:54,240
Maybe a miracle could happen.

334
00:27:55,400 --> 00:27:59,240
Days like this are what faith is for.

335
00:28:00,120 --> 00:28:01,880
We need to believe.

336
00:28:04,800 --> 00:28:07,320
We’ve seen the impossible already.

337
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:11,200
Let’s believe in Singha and Thup
a little more.

338
00:28:37,600 --> 00:28:39,560
You remember me, right, Mom.

339
00:28:39,760 --> 00:28:41,360
I’m Thup.

340
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:44,000
I came with Singha back then.

341
00:28:45,040 --> 00:28:46,480
I remember.

342
00:28:47,440 --> 00:28:48,960
I’m sorry, Mom.

343
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:52,720
I couldn’t protect Singha.

344
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:59,960
He’s badly hurt in the hospital now.

345
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:03,240
He’s been unconscious for hours.

346
00:29:08,240 --> 00:29:10,400
Wait here for me, my child.

347
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:44,000
Please perform a soul-calling ritual
for Singha.

348
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:47,320
He’s lost his way right now.

349
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:51,440
Or waiting for someone to call him.

350
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:54,760
Help me call Singha back.

351
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:57,000
Bring him back to Thup.

352
00:29:57,720 --> 00:30:00,520
So he can wake up, my child.

353
00:30:02,520 --> 00:30:05,360
Aren’t you going to see Singha.

354
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:07,920
I can’t.

355
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:10,000
I have to stay here.

356
00:30:10,320 --> 00:30:13,960
But the one Singha wants to see most
right now is you.

357
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:18,400
When Maysa passed away,

358
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:22,880
Singha fell ill from blaming himself.

359
00:30:23,120 --> 00:30:25,440
He was hospitalized many times.

360
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:27,920
The doctors couldn’t find the cause.

361
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:31,320
So I prayed to Thao Wessuwan.

362
00:30:32,120 --> 00:30:36,360
I asked him to protect Singha’s life.

363
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:38,880
In return, I renounced the world.

364
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:42,600
I devoted myself to making merit,

365
00:30:42,840 --> 00:30:44,760
and I will stay here for life.

366
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:46,560
I won’t go anywhere.

367
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:51,400
The one who can call Singha home

368
00:30:51,560 --> 00:30:53,400
is not me.

369
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:58,240
The place Singha calls home now

370
00:30:58,760 --> 00:31:00,800
is you, Thup.

371
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:07,960
Yes, Mom.

372
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:12,600
I’ll bring Singha back to you.

373
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:15,680
Thank you, my child.

374
00:31:35,960 --> 00:31:37,720
Oh spirit, where are you.

375
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:39,480
Where have you gone to hide.

376
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:42,760
Return to your body and self.

377
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:45,160
Return to your family.

378
00:31:45,720 --> 00:31:47,120
Return to our home.

379
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:50,520
Come back, dear spirit.

380
00:31:51,600 --> 00:31:52,920
Don’t be afraid.

381
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:54,600
Don’t cry.

382
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:57,320
Where is your spirit.

383
00:31:58,120 --> 00:31:59,680
Please come back.

384
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:03,360
Oh spirit, where are you.

385
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:05,920
Where have you gone to hide.

386
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:08,880
Return to your body and self.

387
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:11,240
Return to your family.

388
00:32:11,800 --> 00:32:13,360
Return to our home.

389
00:32:14,640 --> 00:32:16,520
Come back, dear spirit.

390
00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:20,080
Don’t be afraid, don’t cry.

391
00:32:21,320 --> 00:32:22,920
Where is your spirit.

392
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:25,440
Please come back.

393
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:28,800
Come back to Thup, Sing.

394
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:55,040
Am I already dead.

395
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:57,960
You didn’t do anything wrong.

396
00:32:58,520 --> 00:33:00,560
Please stop blaming yourself.

397
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:03,840
I have to go now.

398
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:18,040
But you can’t come with me yet.

399
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:20,800
You need to go to the one waiting for you.

400
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:23,760
The one I believe

401
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:27,520
will take good care of you, Singha.

402
00:33:32,040 --> 00:33:34,960
Mom said one day we’ll meet again.

403
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:38,200
Let’s meet again on that day.

404
00:34:45,600 --> 00:34:47,480
Singha still hasn’t woken up.

405
00:34:48,719 --> 00:34:49,960
Earlier

406
00:34:51,159 --> 00:34:52,920
the doctor told me

407
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:56,760
they’re moving Singha to another ward.

408
00:34:57,080 --> 00:34:58,480
They’re changing his treatment

409
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:01,200
to palliative care.

410
00:35:08,640 --> 00:35:10,000
Sey.

411
00:35:11,160 --> 00:35:13,000
Don’t say it like that, man.

412
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:19,520
Sometimes it’s time to accept the truth.

413
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:25,960
The happy ending you’re hoping for

414
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:29,560
might not exist.

415
00:35:31,440 --> 00:35:32,720
Doctor,

416
00:35:33,280 --> 00:35:36,120
you don’t have to say everything you think.

417
00:35:49,240 --> 00:35:50,640
Singha.

418
00:35:50,640 --> 00:35:52,000
Singha.

419
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:53,560
Wake up.

420
00:35:53,560 --> 00:35:55,320
You need to wake up now.

421
00:35:57,240 --> 00:35:59,040
I’m telling you to wake up.

422
00:36:00,320 --> 00:36:02,200
Singha, wake up.

423
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:06,120
Wake up and talk to me.

424
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:09,800
You’re really not getting up, are you.

425
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:14,240
Get up and talk to me, please.

426
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:15,720
Singha.

427
00:36:18,640 --> 00:36:19,880
Sey, Darin.

428
00:36:20,160 --> 00:36:22,000
Help me wake Singha up.

429
00:36:22,160 --> 00:36:23,880
So he can wake up.

430
00:36:24,240 --> 00:36:25,760
I won’t let you go anywhere.

431
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:29,600
I’m still waiting for that seven-days,
seven-nights post from you.

432
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:31,560
The one saying we’re a couple.

433
00:36:37,200 --> 00:36:39,280
You love teasing me like this.

434
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:43,720
Are you not keeping your promise.

435
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:47,640
Singha.

436
00:36:52,560 --> 00:36:54,200
If you don’t wake up,

437
00:36:54,640 --> 00:36:56,600
I swear I’ll never have anyone else.

438
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:01,400
Singha.

439
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:20,240
Just now you said

440
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:23,360
you’d leave me for someone else.

441
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:36,560
- Singha.
- Sing.

442
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:39,600
Singha.

443
00:37:39,720 --> 00:37:41,760
Singha.

444
00:37:43,720 --> 00:37:45,120
Singha.

445
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:47,640
You really woke up, right.

446
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:49,120
Singha.

447
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:13,760
Wednesday, Thursday, Friday,
Saturday, Sunday.

448
00:38:14,360 --> 00:38:16,480
But we don’t have all seven.

449
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:19,640
We have to kill more to help Dad.
Bring everyone.

450
00:38:19,920 --> 00:38:21,600
Seven people, kill them.

451
00:38:21,640 --> 00:38:22,920
Help Dad.

452
00:38:22,960 --> 00:38:25,440
We have to help Dad.
He’s very sick.

453
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:27,920
Dad is sick. We have to help him.

454
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:31,280
Bom has lupus.

455
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:34,480
It’s an autoimmune disease
he’s had since birth.

456
00:38:34,800 --> 00:38:38,120
That’s why he was in and out
of the hospital so often.

457
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:41,200
So his father kept using rituals
to extend his life.

458
00:38:42,200 --> 00:38:44,200
The doctors concluded

459
00:38:44,240 --> 00:38:46,640
he had severe mental issues.

460
00:38:49,520 --> 00:38:53,240
Maybe if Bom didn’t have
a father like Aisoon,

461
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:56,640
he might not have chosen
this wrong path.

462
00:38:58,920 --> 00:39:00,520
You reap what you sow.

463
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:03,880
No one could save him.

464
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:09,360
What can he even do to us.

465
00:39:09,360 --> 00:39:10,680
He had to help his dad.

466
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:14,040
Hey. Hey.

467
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:15,480
Please help my dad.

468
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:18,160
Please help my dad.

469
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:22,760
I already killed seven people.

470
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:25,160
I followed every step of the plan.

471
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:28,440
So why isn’t my dad better.

472
00:39:28,880 --> 00:39:30,400
Just arrest him already.

473
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:34,240
No. Push him away.

474
00:39:38,080 --> 00:39:40,040
Get out. Get out.

475
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:45,960
No. No. Get out. Get out.

476
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:50,320
So you’re moving back.

477
00:39:51,400 --> 00:39:52,680
Yeah.

478
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:56,520
Starting tomorrow,
I’m back at HQ.

479
00:39:57,320 --> 00:39:59,960
You won’t stay to finish
Bom’s case first.

480
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:03,080
You’ve earned your credit too.

481
00:40:06,120 --> 00:40:07,720
I don’t think so.

482
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:12,200
I don’t want to work
just to save face anymore.

483
00:40:13,520 --> 00:40:15,440
I’m going back to my own cases.

484
00:40:15,640 --> 00:40:17,520
Back to where I belong.

485
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:20,520
Honestly, we could still be friends.

486
00:40:25,600 --> 00:40:27,440
But if I keep staying in touch,

487
00:40:27,720 --> 00:40:29,680
I won’t be able to move on from you.

488
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:33,960
When I finally make peace with it,

489
00:40:35,160 --> 00:40:36,760
then we can be friends again.

490
00:40:39,640 --> 00:40:42,160
And I won’t be wishing you and Thup

491
00:40:42,200 --> 00:40:44,040
a long-lasting love either.

492
00:40:44,320 --> 00:40:46,880
If you ever break up,
don’t think of me.

493
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:52,840
Still, I’m glad we got to work together.

494
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:29,320
That the kids survived

495
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:33,360
is thanks to merit
and sacred protection, my children.

496
00:41:36,080 --> 00:41:37,600
I’ll stay here.

497
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:41,400
If anything happens,
come back to me, my child.

498
00:41:44,440 --> 00:41:45,840
Mom.

499
00:41:47,120 --> 00:41:48,680
I know I shouldn’t,

500
00:41:49,320 --> 00:41:51,600
but may I hug you just once.

501
00:41:59,280 --> 00:42:01,360
You’re my only son,

502
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:04,560
the one I’ll love the most forever.

503
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:09,200
But from now on,
you won’t be alone anymore.

504
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:13,200
Does that mean you’ll take Thup
as another son too.

505
00:42:13,720 --> 00:42:15,160
Teasing even at a temple.

506
00:42:16,520 --> 00:42:18,440
But Darin’s right, isn’t she.

507
00:42:20,240 --> 00:42:21,440
Mom.

508
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:23,600
Tomorrow is Thup’s birthday.

509
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:24,840
Please bless him for us.

510
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:27,160
A blessing from an elder
would mean a lot.

511
00:42:30,720 --> 00:42:33,960
I wish Thup a good life,

512
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:35,480
filled with happiness.

513
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:37,600
No matter what you face,

514
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:41,560
may you always carry light
within you.

515
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:43,840
Alright, my child.

516
00:42:45,880 --> 00:42:47,360
Thank you, Mom.

517
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:55,880
You’re my child now.

518
00:42:57,080 --> 00:42:58,440
Yes, Mom.

519
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:03,600
I’ll bring Singha to visit you
every month.

520
00:43:08,520 --> 00:43:11,320
If any couple has a happy event,

521
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:14,200
let me know.

522
00:43:14,840 --> 00:43:17,240
I’ll consult the monks
for an auspicious date.

523
00:43:18,560 --> 00:43:20,240
Thank you, Mom.

524
00:43:21,400 --> 00:43:22,760
Mom.

525
00:43:54,480 --> 00:43:57,960
My child, don’t come in.

526
00:43:58,400 --> 00:44:00,080
You’ll be scared.

527
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:10,600
I’m not scared.

528
00:44:23,600 --> 00:44:25,480
I used to think,

529
00:44:27,360 --> 00:44:30,560
that I was unlucky
to live this kind of life.

530
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:34,440
Seeing ghosts.

531
00:44:35,880 --> 00:44:37,320
Being an orphan.

532
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:41,000
And feeling unwanted.

533
00:44:42,320 --> 00:44:44,080
But the truth is,

534
00:44:45,680 --> 00:44:47,120
I have a mother.

535
00:44:48,080 --> 00:44:49,720
A mother who sacrificed everything.

536
00:44:50,240 --> 00:44:52,880
Who did whatever it took
to protect me.

537
00:44:59,560 --> 00:45:02,160
And someone who loved me,

538
00:45:04,920 --> 00:45:06,120
all because of you, Mom.

539
00:45:18,080 --> 00:45:20,280
May I hug you, Mom.

540
00:46:07,520 --> 00:46:09,360
I love you, Mom.

541
00:46:41,400 --> 00:46:42,720
Thup.

542
00:47:14,400 --> 00:47:17,480
Didn’t you say you’d post us
for seven days straight.

543
00:47:17,880 --> 00:47:19,400
Come on.

544
00:47:19,760 --> 00:47:23,240
It’s time the inspector tells the world
he’s dating a younger guy.

545
00:47:23,880 --> 00:47:26,600
When I give my word,
I keep it.

546
00:47:26,720 --> 00:47:28,640
I can post for a hundred days
if you want.

547
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:31,040
Come here.

548
00:47:43,080 --> 00:47:44,600
Did you get it in time.

549
00:47:47,600 --> 00:47:48,960
Did I.

550
00:47:49,920 --> 00:47:51,240
Satisfied now.

551
00:47:52,440 --> 00:47:53,760
That’s it.

552
00:47:53,880 --> 00:47:56,840
Next time you want anything, just tell me.

553
00:47:57,200 --> 00:47:59,080
Consider it a birthday gift.

554
00:47:59,320 --> 00:48:01,040
You said it yourself.

555
00:48:02,040 --> 00:48:03,240
Yeah.

556
00:48:04,920 --> 00:48:06,760
Can I take off the cat ears yet?

557
00:48:07,600 --> 00:48:09,400
Why would you take them off?

558
00:48:09,960 --> 00:48:11,360
Cat ears.

559
00:48:11,440 --> 00:48:12,840
They suit you so much.

560
00:48:13,000 --> 00:48:14,440
